# InferTest — expected entailments
# Construct : ObjectPropertyAssertion over a multi-level subproperty hierarchy
#
# Alice is only asserted Bob's biological mother. A conformant reasoner
# must also relate them through EVERY broader property in the chain
# (isMotherOf, isParentOf, isAncestorOf, isRelatedTo) — not just the one
# directly asserted. Missing any one of these means the reasoner (or your
# pipeline's materialisation step) isn't walking the full subproperty
# hierarchy.

@prefix : <http://example.org/infertest#> .

:ObjectPropertyAssertion_Alice :objectPropertyAssertionIsMotherOf :ObjectPropertyAssertion_Bob .
:ObjectPropertyAssertion_Alice :objectPropertyAssertionIsParentOf :ObjectPropertyAssertion_Bob .
:ObjectPropertyAssertion_Alice :objectPropertyAssertionIsAncestorOf :ObjectPropertyAssertion_Bob .
:ObjectPropertyAssertion_Alice :objectPropertyAssertionIsRelatedTo :ObjectPropertyAssertion_Bob .
